Sentencas: A cobalt-free perovskite oxide, Ba0.5Sr0.5Zn0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (BSZF), was investigated as a novel cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Zn0.2Fe0.8O3-δ perovskite oxide as a novel cathode for intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Room-temperature nonstoichiometry of BSZF was as high as 0.412, which was favorable for oxygen-reduction reaction.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Zn0.2Fe0.8O3-δ perovskite oxide as a novel cathode for intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 700 degrees C, the polarization resistances were as low as 0.22 and 0.13 Omega.cm(2), respectively, for pure and impregnated BSZF cathodes under open-circuit conditions, suggesting that oxygen-deficient BSZF was a promising cathode candidate for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Zn0.2Fe0.8O3-δ perovskite oxide as a novel cathode for intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells
